NOTE FOR ANY LEGAL TEAMS: This repository has adopted CC BY-SA 4.0 International/Unported for the documentation
materials (aka Markdown files in the docs directory, minus any embedded content which may use more stricter licensing)
and the premissive MIT license. This placeholder has been added to ensure both GitHub and GitLab will know about this
situtation. Please read the included legal code we checked in to version control for your reference.

This open-source project has implemented two seperate licenses to sepreate concerns regarding using one license
for everything. To determine under which license you may use a file from this repository, please resort to the README
file of an specific directory in question.

1. Markdown files in the docs directory are licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 Unported or
   later, check the License.cc-by-sa.txt file we provided in this repository root. In case these files aren't included
   in an fork/mirror, please visit https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/legalcode.
2. The rest of the repository will use the MIT license, see the License.mit.txt file for full legal code.

When in doubt, please contact the project maintainers listed in the MAINTAINERS.md file, either directly or thrrough the
public issue tracker at https://gitlab.cm/Community-Lores/glossary/issues and they'll gladly help you. Please be reminded
that we're not legal experts, so please take it with an grain of salt.

